answerText: Crab Nebula [prompt on M1, accept New General Catalogue 1952, accept but DO NOT MENTION IF IT IS NOT GIVEN: Taurus A][10] The Crab Nebula is located in this zodiac constellation of the Northern hemisphere, as are the Hyades and Pleiades star clusters. It also contains the red giant star Aldebaran.

question: Question: This remant of a supernova was first spotted in the year 1054 CE by Chinese astronomers. For 10 points each: [10] Name this object consisting of a blue-white cloud of electrons surrounding a pulsar core. It is the first object in the Messier catalogue.
